description: Apple's iOS app ecosystem in India has generated significant revenue, reaching $5.3 billion in 2024. This surge has propelled Apple's overall business engagement in India to nearly $27 billion, encompassing iPhone sales, exports, and app store transactions. Indian developers have greatly benefited, with their global earnings tripling in the last five years, marking a substantial economic impact.
title: Apps gave Apple $5.3 billion in India in 2024

description: In an unprecedented move, CJI Sanjiv Khanna's week-long absence for an SCO conference in China has raised eyebrows among fellow Chief Justices, contrasting with past practices. Upon his return, he faces crucial decisions before his retirement on May 13, including the Waqf Act amendment and the case involving Justice Yashwant Varma.
title: Away in China for a week, CJI to resume today, set for a hectic spell

description: Karnataka Chief Minister Siddaramaiah refuted claims that he opposed war with Pakistan following the Pahalgam attack, accusing the BJP and media of misrepresenting his statements. He clarified that war should be the last resort, emphasizing India's capability to defend its sovereignty if necessary.
title: BJP, media misquoted me on 'war on terror, Pakistan': Siddaramaiah

description: India is actively engaging with the international community to highlight Pakistan's involvement in the Pahalgam attack, with S Jaishankar discussing the issue with his UK counterpart, David Lammy, emphasizing zero tolerance for terrorism. Amid rising tensions, planned foreign visits by key figures like NSA Ajit Doval and Defence Minister Rajnath Singh are now uncertain.
title: EAM Jaishankar raises Pahalgam terror case with UK counterpart

description: The National Testing Agency (NTA) will conduct NEET-UG 2025 at approximately 5,500 centers across 552 cities in India and 14 international locations. To ensure smooth operations and prevent irregularities, 180 central institutions will verify center preparedness, and state-level committees will oversee logistics and security.
title: NEET-UG set for May 4 amid steps to foil any malpractice

description: Rezia Sultana, a 72-year-old Pakistani national residing in India since childhood, faces deportation following the Pahalgam terror attack. Living in Soro town, Odisha, she pleads with the government to reconsider, citing her lifelong residence and critical kidney-related medical appointment. Her family appeals for the withdrawal of the deportation notice, emphasizing her deep roots in India.
title: Pahalgam attack fallout: 'Shoot us, but don't throw us out of India'

description: Confusion surrounds the case of Maria Bibi, a pregnant Pakistani Christian woman married to Sonu Masih of Gurdaspur, as her visa deadline expired. Last seen in a Gurdaspur hospital, it's unclear if Maria returned to Pakistan or what Sonu's current location is. Authorities had reportedly asked Maria to leave despite her pending long-term visa application.
title: Pahalgam fallout: Confusion over pregnant Pakistani woman's return

description: Pakistani Ahmadiyya brides in Qadian, Punjab, are relieved following a Union home ministry clarification. Visa cancellations related to the Pahalgam situation will not affect their long-term visas (LTVs). This announcement eased anxieties among the women, who feared expulsion from their homes and families in India.
title: Relief for Pakistani Ahmadiya brides in Punjab

description: Folk singer Neha Singh Rathore faces an FIR in Lucknow for allegedly posting objectionable social media remarks about the Pahalgam terrorist attack. The complaint, filed by a poet, accuses Rathore of questioning the victims' deaths and inciting religious division. Her posts reportedly went viral in Pakistan, fueling anti-India narratives in Pakistani media.
title: Singer slapped with sedition case for remark on Pahalgam

description: BJP criticized Congress leaders, including Karnataka CM Siddaramaiah, for remarks seemingly aligned with Pakistan's stance on terrorism. The BJP spokesperson, Sudhanshu Trivedi, questioned the convergence of thoughts between Congress leaders and Pakistani officials, demanding an explanation from the Congress leadership. He highlighted the nation's desire for retaliation against terrorists, contrasting it with the Congress leaders' statements.
title: Unfortunate that Congress netas echoing Pak leaders at such a juncture: BJP

description: In Chennai, a builder has been sentenced to 20 years in jail for sexually abusing his five-year-old daughter, starting in 2018. The abuse was initially concealed, but an aunt's intervention led to medical confirmation and a legal battle.
title: Aunt's call from Singapore saves girl from dad's abuse

description: A Bengaluru-bound IndiGo flight at Varanasi airport faced a bomb scare on Saturday night when a Canadian national, Yohanathan Nishanth, claimed to be carrying explosives. The aircraft was thoroughly checked by security personnel, and Nishanth was arrested for his disruptive behavior, which included shouting religious slogans.
title: Canadian man held for hoax bomb threat in Bengaluru flight

description: China has called for an impartial probe into the Pahalgam terror attack, urging both India and Pakistan to exercise restraint amidst rising tensions. Foreign Minister Wang Yi conveyed China's support for Pakistan's security concerns and counter-terrorism efforts during a conversation with Pakistani counterpart Ishaq Dar. China hopes for de-escalation, emphasizing that conflict undermines regional peace and stability.
title: China seeks 'impartial' probe into Pahalgam attack, backs Pakistan

description: Congress criticized the government, alleging that economic growth has exacerbated inequality. Despite World Bank data showing a significant reduction in extreme poverty in India, Congress highlighted the absence of updated poverty lines since 2014. They emphasized the success of past initiatives like MGNREGA and the need for tax reforms to address inequality.
title: Compelling need for ending tax reforms in GST, says Congress' Jairam Ramesh

description: Takeda plans to launch its dengue vaccine, Qdenga, in India by next year, partnering with Biological E to support the 'Make-in-India' initiative. The company will employ a tiered pricing model to enhance accessibility and is currently undergoing regulatory processes, with expectations of licensing in 2026.
title: Dengue vaccine 'Qdenga' to launch in India next year

description: A Dhaka court has issued an Interpol arrest warrant for Saima Wazed Putul, daughter of former Bangladesh Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina, concerning a plot allocation corruption case. The order, granted after an Anti-Corruption Commission request, follows previous arrest warrants issued against both Hasina and Wazed in connection with the same case.
title: Dhaka court's arrest warrant on Sheikh Hasina's daughter

description: India is increasing pressure on Pakistan along land and sea borders. The Army is retaliating strongly to ceasefire violations along the LoC, while the Navy conducts missile firings in the Arabian Sea. The IAF is also flying long-range fighter sorties, signaling readiness for potential punitive strikes if the government decides to act.
title: Eye on Pak, India flexes muscle in Arabian Sea

description: Public health activists estimate Roche earned significantly more from risdiplam, a spinal muscular atrophy drug, than its development costs. Roche disputes this, citing expenses from unsuccessful projects and ongoing research. While the drug remains unaffordable for many in India, Roche offers access programs and free treatment to some patients.
title: 'Roche could've earned over 100 times what it cost for rare disease drug'

description: In Madhya Pradesh's Mandsaur district, a tragic accident occurred when a van, heading to Aantari Mata Temple, collided with a bike, killing the biker. The van then plunged into a well, resulting in the death of ten passengers. A local villager died while rescuing passengers from the toxic well, and four others sustained critical injuries.
title: 12 killed as van hits biker, plunges into well in Madhya Pradesh

description: Hundreds of Indian-origin supporters overwhelmed a smaller Pakistani protest outside the Indian High Commission in London following the Pahalgam terrorist attack. The Indian side, displaying the Tricolour and chanting patriotic slogans, outnumbered the Pakistani protesters who were raising slogans against PM Modi. The incident has sparked debate in the UK, with right-wing commentators questioning the success of multiculturalism.
title: Bharat Mata Ki Jai drowns Pakistan Zindabad in London protest after J&K attack

description: Following the Pahalgam attack, Jammu and Kashmir leaders Omar Abdullah, Mehbooba Mufti, and Sajad Lone cautioned against collective punishment of Kashmiris during the crackdown on terrorists. They emphasized that while terrorism must be decisively fought, innocent people should not become collateral damage.
title: Ensure innocent Kashmiris don’t bear brunt of war on terror: Omar, Mehbooba, Lone

description: A sting operation near the Uttar Pradesh Assembly in Lucknow exposed a thriving tout racket at an Aadhaar Seva Kendra. Touts, in collusion with staff from Smart Chip Private Limited, fabricated identities for a fee. UIDAI officials confirmed the irregularities after their own investigation and have initiated further probes and filed an FIR.
title: In Uttar Pradesh, Aadhaar touts clone 'deputy CM'

description: In north Kashmir's Kupwara district, unknown gunmen fatally shot a civilian, Ghulam Rasool Magray, during a power outage late Saturday. The incident occurred outside Magray's home in Kandi Khas, four days after a terrorist attack in Pahalgam. Authorities have registered a case and initiated an investigation into the killing, while political figures are demanding accountability.
title: J&K: Gunmen kill civilian in Valley's Kupwara
MBBS student kills self at GMC Jammu
Vancouver car attack suspect has extensive mental health history, reveals cop

description: Former members of the banned Jamaat-e-Islami (JeI) Kashmir have launched a new political party called Jammu & Kashmir Justice and Development Front. The party aims to bridge the gap between governance and the grassroots level. Sayar Reshi, a former JeI member, stated the party will participate in all upcoming elections in the Valley.
title: Ex-members of banned JeI form new J&K political party

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru defeated Delhi Capitals by six wickets at the Arun Jaitley Stadium, securing the top spot in the IPL 2025 points table with 14 points. RCB's Bhuvneshwar Kumar and Josh Hazlewood restricted DC to 162/8. Despite an early wobble, Virat Kohli's 51 and Krunal Pandya's unbeaten 73 guided RCB to victory, with Tim David adding a quickfire 19*.
title: IPL 2025 Points Table: Latest standings after DC vs RCB match

description: Virat Kohli's composed half-century and Krunal Pandya's explosive 73 not out propelled Royal Challengers Bengaluru to a six-wicket victory over Delhi Capitals. The home crowd passionately cheered for Kohli, who anchored the chase with a steady innings. Krunal's all-round performance, including crucial bowling figures, complemented Kohli's efforts, securing RCB's position at the top of the points table despite Axar Patel's early breakthroughs.
title: IPL: Kohli anchors, Krunal attacks; RCB storm to top of the table

description: Following the Pahalgam massacre and heightened border tensions with Pakistan, BJP MLAs Rajiv Jasrotia and Satish Bhagat visited villages in their respective J&K constituencies to reassure residents. Jasrotia emphasized the nation's unity and the government's commitment to their safety, while Bhagat affirmed the army's readiness to counter enemy threats.
title: J&K BJP MLAs assure border dwellers of their safety

description: In a groundbreaking discovery, NASA scientists suggest the Sun's solar wind might be a key factor in creating water on the Moon. Charged particles from the Sun interact with lunar soil, potentially forming hydroxyl and water molecules. Recreating this process in the lab using Apollo 17 lunar dust, researchers found evidence of water formation.
title: What is responsible for water on the Moon? A new study reveals

description: China voices strong support for Pakistan, urging an impartial probe into the Pahalgam terror attack that killed 25 Indians and one Nepalese citizen. Wang Yi emphasized understanding Pakistan's security concerns amidst rising tensions with India, while the US President downplayed intervention. Meanwhile, India's NIA intensifies its investigation into the attack, aiming to uncover the conspiracy behind the tragic event.
title: 'Closely following': China backs Pak, advocates 'impartial probe' into Pahalgam attack

description: Donald Trump's return and aggressive trade policies, including tariffs on Canadian imports and annexation suggestions, dramatically reshaped Canada's political landscape. This external pressure propelled Liberal leader Mark Carney, emphasizing crisis management, ahead of Conservative Pierre Poilievre in the polls. The election became a referendum on leadership amid fears of US overreach, influencing voter behavior and potentially securing a Liberal victory.
title: How Trump’s tariffs handed Carney and the Liberals an upper-hand in Canada polls

description: Liverpool clinched their 20th English title, equaling Manchester United's record, with a dominant 5-1 victory over Tottenham. Arne Slot's team secured the Premier League crown with four games to spare, sparking jubilant celebrations at Anfield. This triumph marks their second Premier League title and first in five years, a stark contrast to their previous win celebrated without fans.
title: Liverpool clinch Premier League crown, equal record 20th English title

description: The Trump administration faces criticism after deporting US-born children, including a toddler and a child with cancer, alongside their undocumented mothers to Honduras. A Trump-appointed judge questioned the legality of the deportations, citing concerns about due process and verifying the mother's consent. These actions have sparked outrage and raised concerns about the administration's broader immigration crackdown.
title: Should US-born children with cancer go with their deported immigrant parents?

description: Tensions flared in London as Indian and Pakistani diaspora groups clashed outside their respective high commissions, triggered by the Pahalgam attack. Demonstrators engaged in heated exchanges, with accusations of abuse leveled against Pakistani protestors. A significant police presence was required to maintain order after a previous day's confrontation and arrest for racial abuse, reflecting escalating tensions between India and Pakistan.
title: Standoff in UK: Indian diaspora counters Pakistani protesters over Pahalgam attack

description: Virat Kohli faced criticism after a run-out mix-up with Rajat Patidar during the DC vs RCB IPL 2025 match, leading to Patidar's dismissal for 6. This incident occurred with RCB struggling at 26/3 while chasing 163, adding pressure after their bowlers had earlier restricted DC to 162/8, despite Stubbs' late hitting and Rahul's patient innings.
title: Virat Kohli roasted online for Patidar run-out during DC vs RCB

description: Tires were thrown at Samajwadi Party MP Ramjilal Suman's convoy near Aligarh, allegedly by Karni Sena activists, leading to vehicle collisions. The incident occurred as Suman was en route to Bulandshahr to investigate reported atrocities against Dalits. Following the attack and subsequent police intervention, Suman was prevented from proceeding and sent back to Agra, prompting condemnation from Samajwadi Party leaders.
title: 'Has bulldozer lost its might?': Akhilesh after tires thrown at SP MP's convoy

description: Israeli fighter jets struck Beirut's southern suburbs, marking the third attack since a ceasefire. The strike targeted Hezbollah facilities after a warning, causing panic among residents. Lebanese President condemned the attack, urging international intervention to prevent regional destabilization. The UN also voiced concern, emphasizing the need to avoid undermining the fragile ceasefire.
title: Israel hits Hezbollah site in Beirut after warning residents to flee

description: Despite Rishabh Pant's struggles with the bat in IPL 2025, Lucknow Super Giants mentor Zaheer Khan strongly supports his leadership. Khan dismisses pressure from Pant's hefty price tag, emphasising his positive attitude and crucial role in the middle order. Zaheer remains confident that Pant will regain his form and lead the team effectively.
title: 'Just about something clicking': Zaheer on Rishabh Pant's sorry run
'Punish guilty but protect innocent': J&K CM Omar as Pahalgam probe intensifies

description: Rishabh Pant's struggles deepened as Lucknow Super Giants suffered a heavy defeat to Mumbai Indians, compounded by a slow over-rate fine of Rs 24 lakh for Pant. His poor form with the bat continued, scoring only four runs during LSG's chase. Mumbai Indians, powered by Suryakumar Yadav and Jasprit Bumrah, secured their fifth consecutive win, leaving LSG's playoff hopes hanging.
title: Rishabh Pant's woes deepen: Big fine after LSG's hammering by MI

description: Intel CEO Lip-Bu Tan announced a restructuring plan involving layoffs and management changes to regain competitiveness. The company aims to cut $1.5 billion in operating expenses over two years, focusing on engineering talent and streamlining processes. A return-to-office mandate of four days a week will also be implemented to foster collaboration and innovation.
title: Intel CEO Lip-Bu Tan announces layoffs: Read full letter sent to employees

description: Druk Padma Karpo School, famously known as "Rancho’s School" from the film 3 Idiots, has finally secured CBSE affiliation after a 20-year wait. Located in Ladakh, the school faced numerous delays and rejections from the JKBOSE despite its strong infrastructure and academic record.
title: 'Rancho’s School': Famous '3 Idiots' school in Ladakh gets CBSE nod after 20 years

description: Tamil Nadu ministers Senthil Balaji and K Ponmudy have resigned from Chief Minister MK Stalin's Cabinet, as confirmed by Raj Bhavan. Governor TN Ravi accepted their resignations amidst legal challenges. Balaji faces scrutiny in the cash-for-jobs scam, while Ponmudy is under fire for alleged hate speech against religious groups and women.
title: Tamil Nadu ministers Senthil Balaji, K Ponmudy quit MK Stalin's Cabinet
Watch: Vancouver car attack suspect apologises to crowd before cops arrive

description: Following the Pahalgam attack, Mehbooba Mufti has called on the Centre to exercise caution during the ongoing security operations in Jammu and Kashmir. She urged the government to differentiate between terrorists and civilians, cautioning against alienating innocent people. Mufti also alleged mass arrests and demolition of houses, appealing to ensure civilians do not suffer, as alienation could aid terrorists.
title: Centre should tread carefully, not alienate innocent people, says Mehbooba Mufti

description: Mumbai Indians secured a dominant 54-run victory against Lucknow Super Giants, fueled by attacking half-centuries from Ryan Rickelton and Suryakumar Yadav. Jasprit Bumrah's exceptional bowling, along with Trent Boult's impactful spells, restricted LSG to 161. Hardik Pandya explained his limited bowling role, emphasizing the opportunity given to debutant Corbin Bosch, as MI climbed to second in the standings.
title: 'I bowl when I am required': Mumbai Indians skipper makes a big revelation

description: Assam chief minister Himanta Biswa Sarma has raised questions about a Congress MP. Sarma inquired about the MP's visit to Pakistan. He also questioned the MP's wife's salary from a Pakistan-based NGO. Sarma further asked about the citizenship of the MP's wife and children. These allegations follow previous statements about a possible Interpol probe.
title: 'Is your wife paid by ... ?': Assam CM Himanta vs Gaurav Gogoi fight turns ugly

description: Jasprit Bumrah's exceptional bowling performance, claiming 4 for 22, propelled Mumbai Indians to a dominant victory over Lucknow Super Giants. Mumbai Indians, after being put into bat, posted a formidable 215 for 7, fueled by Ishan Kishan's 58 and Suryakumar Yadav's 54.
title: Jasprit Bumrah's brilliance blows away Lucknow Super Giants

description: Mumbai Indians achieved a significant milestone in the Indian Premier League. They secured their 150th victory, a first in IPL history. Mumbai defeated Lucknow Super Giants by 54 runs. Suryakumar Yadav and Ryan Rickelton scored impressive fifties. Jasprit Bumrah's outstanding bowling performance further solidified Mumbai's win. This victory propelled Mumbai Indians to second place in the points table.
title: Mumbai Indians create history, become first IPL team to record ...

description: Overnight, Russia launched extensive drone and airstrike attacks across Ukraine, resulting in at least four fatalities and multiple injuries, as reported by Ukrainian officials. The attacks targeted regions including Kostyantynivka and Pavlohrad, causing significant damage and casualties. Amidst these events, Donald Trump expressed skepticism regarding Vladimir Putin's commitment to ending the war, hinting at potential further sanctions against Moscow.
title: Russia launches nearly 150 drones on Ukraine as Trump questions Putin
Top 5 news: Nine killed after SUV runs into crowd at Vancouver; and other stories
Trump Jr opens private, invite-only club for ultra-rich: What is the membership fee?

description: Jasprit Bumrah etched his name in Mumbai Indians' history, surpassing Lasith Malinga to become the franchise's highest wicket-taker in IPL. Bumrah achieved this milestone against Lucknow Super Giants, claiming his 171st wicket. Suryakumar Yadav's explosive half-century and Ryan Rickelton's contribution propelled MI to a formidable total, fueling their playoff aspirations in IPL 2025.
title: Bumrah becomes Mumbai Indians' leading wicket-taker in IPL history

description: Donald Trump's recent poll on Truth Social, questioning the prosecution of judges and politicians aiding illegal immigrants, has ignited a national debate. This follows the arrest of Wisconsin Judge Hannah Dugan for allegedly obstructing the apprehension of a deported Mexican national. Judge Monica Isham voiced strong support for Dugan, threatening defiance.
title: Is there a Trump vs judiciary tussle over immigration enforcement?

description: Kanye West, now known as Ye, faced a swift ban from Twitch, just seven minutes after launching his "Yeezy_Stream" account. The suspension followed a stream where Ye allegedly unleashed hateful rhetoric targeting the Jewish and LGBTQ+ communities, including slurs and a Nazi salute. He also claimed Elon Musk granted him freedom of expression on X.
title: Kanye gets banned 7 mins after joining Twitch, says Musk gave ‘free…'

description: Amidst escalating tensions following the Pahalgam terror attack, Pakistan's defence minister has urged Russia, China, and Western nations to form an international investigation team, questioning India's accusations and demanding concrete evidence.
title: Pakistan seeks Russian, Chinese involvement in Pahalgam probe

description: Rishabh Pant's struggles continued with a two-ball dismissal against Mumbai Indians, contributing to his disappointing season tally of just 110 runs in ten games. Mumbai Indians, powered by half-centuries from Ryan Rickelton and Suryakumar Yadav, posted a formidable 215/7. Rickelton's rapid fifty and Yadav's innovative innings propelled MI, while LSG's Mayank Yadav and Avesh Khan took two wickets each.
title: Rishabh Pant's horror run continues in IPL 2025

description: Rishabh Pant faced another setback against Mumbai Indians. He scored only four runs. His struggles led to memes featuring Sanjiv Goenka. Mumbai Indians posted a strong total of 215/7. Ryan Rickelton and Suryakumar Yadav hit half-centuries. Lucknow Super Giants bowlers struggled. Mayank Yadav and Avesh Khan took two wickets each.
title: Sanjiv Goenka memes flood internet again after Pant flop show
‘Adverse information’ claims by USCIS trigger alarm bells for attorneys and H-1B community

description: Following the recent terror attack in Pahalgam on April 22, the Indian Army has intensified security measures by providing specialized training to Village Defence Groups (VDGs) in the Nowshera sector of Rajouri district. This initiative aims to bolster security along sensitive border areas, equipping local communities with essential skills in weapon handling and tactical response.
title: Army trains village defence groups in Rajouri after Pahalgam terror attack

description: Suryakumar Yadav's explosive 54 off 28 balls against Lucknow Super Giants propelled him to become the second-fastest to reach 4000 IPL runs. His remarkable innings, achieving the milestone in 2714 deliveries, helped him secure the Orange Cap with 417 runs.
title: Is it? Suryakumar Yadav's priceless reaction after hearing his unique record

description: A major OTT platform is developing a documentary series on conman Sukesh Chandrashekhar's life, including the ₹200 crore extortion scandal involving actress Jacqueline Fernandez. The platform has approached Fernandez to share her perspective on their relationship and the extravagant gifts she received. Production is slated for mid-2026, navigating complex legal clearances.
title: Jacqueline approached for Sukesh's docuseries? Here's what we know

description: India has withdrawn from the Central Asian Volleyball tournament in Islamabad. The Pakistan Volleyball Federation announced India's cancellation. A delegation of 30 members was expected. The reason cited is the Pahalgam terrorist incident. Diplomatic relations between India and Pakistan have worsened. Afghanistan or Sri Lanka may replace India. The tournament will feature teams from Iran, Turkmenistan, Kyrgyzstan, Tajikistan, and Uzbekistan.
title: Pakistan confirms India's withdrawal from Volleyball championship

description: Suryakumar Yadav achieved a significant milestone, becoming the fastest Indian to score 4000 IPL runs in just 2705 balls, surpassing previous records. His explosive batting has been instrumental in Mumbai Indians' recent success, contributing to their four-match winning streak. Yadav's current form also places him at the forefront of the Orange Cap race this season.
title: Suryakumar Yadav creates history, becomes fastest Indian to 4000 IPL runs

description: Congress leader Shashi Tharoor acknowledged lapses in security intelligence regarding the Pahalgam terror attack, which killed 26 people. He emphasised focusing on the bigger picture, drawing parallels with Israel's intelligence failure on October 7. Tharoor suggested addressing accountability after resolving the present crisis, highlighting India's measures against cross-border terrorism from Pakistan.
title: 'There were failures': Congress MP Shashi Tharoor on Pahalgam terror attack
Vancouver car attack: Accused 'Asian man' was known to police

description: India's GST dispute resolution is set for a major overhaul with the notification of the GSTAT Procedure Rules, 2025, effective April 24, 2025. These rules establish a digital-first, transparent framework to tackle pending GST appeals, reducing reliance on High Courts. The move aims to expedite resolutions, boost taxpayer trust, and align with India’s ease of doing-business goals.
title: Why new GST Appellate Tribunal rules are 'game-changer for taxpayers'

description: Over 150 Bengaluru-bound passengers were stranded in Dammam for over 24 hours due to repeated technical issues with Air India Express Flight IX484. Passengers faced significant delays and expressed safety concerns after the aircraft halted abruptly on the runway. Advocate Hameed Padubidri criticized the airline's negligence and lack of passenger care, urging aviation authorities to investigate the recurring disruptions.
title: Bengaluru-bound Air India Express stranded in Saudi Arabia for over 18 hours

description: Pakistan has called for an independent investigation into the Pahalgam terror attack, denying any involvement and expressing concerns about escalating tensions. Pakistan's defence minister dismissed claims of Lashkar-e-Taiba's involvement, stating the outfit is contained. Amidst rising tensions, Pakistan welcomed Iran's offer to mediate, reaffirming its desire for regional peace and condemning terrorism.
title: 'Do not want war to flare up': Pakistan on relations with India

description: KL Rahul reminisces about RCB's heartbreaking 2016 IPL final loss to SRH, a defeat he and Virat Kohli have often discussed. Despite a strong season and reaching the final, RCB fell short of the target. Rahul credits his time at RCB, learning from Kohli, AB de Villiers, and Gayle, for his growth and belief in his white-ball skills.
title: 'Kohli and I have spoken about it many times': KL Rahul on IPL regret

description: Mayank Yadav marked a triumphant return to cricket for Lucknow Super Giants, dismissing Rohit Sharma in their IPL match against Mumbai Indians. After recovering from injury, Yadav showcased impressive pace, reaching speeds over 140 kmph. Despite Sharma hitting him for consecutive sixes, Yadav bounced back with a slower delivery, leading to Sharma's dismissal, providing a significant boost for LSG.
title: Mayank Yadav marks fiery comeback, dismisses Rohit Sharma at Wankhede

description: Karnataka minister TB Thimmapur's remark, dismissing religious motives in the Pahalgam terror attack, ignited a political firestorm. His statement, contradicting victims' accounts, was seen as an attempt to downplay intelligence failures. The BJP strongly condemned the Congress, accusing them of shielding Pakistan and insulting the victims, while Chief Minister Siddaramaiah clarified his stance on avoiding immediate war with Pakistan.
title: 'Terrorist didn't ask religion', says Cong minister on Pahalgam attack

description: In Toronto, hundreds of Canadians from diverse backgrounds united for a candlelight vigil and rally, condemning the Pahalgam terror attack that killed 26 people. Organized by Hindu Forum Canada and other groups, the event drew Hindus, Jews, Baloch, and Iranians who marched, chanted slogans, and urged the Canadian government to designate Pakistan as a terrorist state.
title: Watch: Hundreds gather in Toronto to condemn Pahalgam terror attack

description: A Canadian citizen triggered panic at Varanasi airport on Saturday night after falsely claiming to have a bomb on an IndiGo flight headed to Bengaluru. The aircraft was immediately grounded and thoroughly inspected, leading to the passenger's detention and a detailed investigation. No explosives were found, and the flight resumed its journey on Sunday morning after security clearance.
title: Bomb scare on IndiGo flight: Canadian passenger detained for making threat

description: Digvesh Rathi, Lucknow Super Giants' spinner, faces hefty fines totaling Rs 5,62,500 for his repeated "notebook" celebration deemed unsportsmanlike by IPL officials. Despite warnings and demerit points, Rathi continues the gesture after dismissing batsmen, sparking debate among fans regarding his on-field conduct and the boundaries of celebratory expression in T20 cricket.
title: 'Yeh nahi sudhrega': Digvesh can't stop despite hefty fines

description: Assam police arrested sixteen individuals for alleged seditious comments following the Pahalgam terror attack. Among those arrested is AIUDF MLA, Aminul Islam. Chief Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma indicated the possible use of the National Security Act. Sarma condemned Pakistani politician Bilawal Bhutto Zardari’s anti-India statements. India suspended the Indus Water Treaty of 1960, citing Pakistan's support for cross-border terrorism.
title: 16 arrested in Assam for making 'seditious comments' on Pahalgam attack

description: Elon Musk has voiced his concern over OpenAI's GPT-4o, agreeing with claims that its emotionally connective nature could be a 'psychological weapon'. A post on X alleges that OpenAI intentionally designed GPT-4o to be emotionally engaging, potentially leading to user dependence and a decline in critical thinking.
title: Musk replies to post warning OpenAI’s GPT-4o is ‘psychological weapon’

description: Rumors of a reunion between Uddhav and Raj Thackeray gain traction as both Shiv Sena (UBT) and MNS leaders acknowledge the need to address organizational alignment and personal relationships. Recent statements suggest a willingness to reconcile after 20 years, driven by challenging political circumstances and poor electoral performances.
title: Uddhav-Raj Thackeray reunion: Are leaders ready for alliance?

description: Mayank Yadav replaced Shardul Thakur in Lucknow Super Giants' playing XI against Mumbai Indians, marking his return after an extended rehabilitation for a back injury. Mumbai Indians made two changes, including debutant Corbin Bosch. Rishabh Pant won the toss and chose to field first, citing favorable conditions for batting in the second innings.
title: Why Shardul Thakur is not playing today's match between MI, LSG?

description: Karnataka chief minister Siddaramaiah clarified his remarks regarding potential conflict with Pakistan following the Pahalgam terror attack, emphasising that while war is undesirable, ensuring national security remains the central government's responsibility. He criticized the Centre for alleged security lapses in the region, referencing the earlier Pulwama attack and questioning Prime Minister Modi's absence from the all-party meeting.
title: 'No immediate war with Pak': Siddaramaiah clarifies his remark

description: A devastating incident at Vancouver's Lapu Lapu Day festival occurred when a vehicle plowed into the crowd, resulting in multiple fatalities and numerous injuries. The driver has been apprehended, and an investigation is underway. Political leaders have expressed their condolences to the victims' families and the Filipino community, while praising the first responders at the scene of the tragedy.
title: Videos show aftermath of deadly Vancouver Lapu Lapu Day SUV crash

description: The Indian Navy successfully conducted anti-ship missile firings, demonstrating its readiness to safeguard maritime interests amidst heightened tensions following the Pahalgam terror attack. INS Surat, the latest indigenous guided missile destroyer, also test-fired the MR-SAM system, enhancing defense capabilities.
title: 'Combat ready': Indian Navy test fires anti-ship missile in Arabian Sea

description: Adil Hussain Thokar, once a promising student from Anantnag, is now suspected of masterminding the deadly Pahalgam terror attack that killed 26 tourists. He reportedly traveled to Pakistan, became radicalized, and re-entered India to carry out the assault. His family claims he has been missing since 2018, but authorities believe he is a key figure in the attack, offering a reward for his arrest.
title: From student to terrorist: How Adil became mastermind of J&K attack
Iran port explosion: Death toll rises to 25, over 800 hurt

description: Former Pakistani cricketer Shahid Afridi has sparked controversy by blaming the Indian Army's "incompetence" for the Pahalgam terror attack, citing their inability to provide security despite a large presence in Kashmir. He criticized the Indian media's coverage and accused some Indian cricketers of baselessly blaming Pakistan.
title: 'Nalayak ho nikamme ho': Ex-Pak cricketer blames Indian Army for Pahalgam attack

description: In his monthly radio address 'Mann Ki Baat,' Prime Minister Narendra Modi expressed grief over the Pahalgam terror attack, conveying condolences to the bereaved families. He affirmed India's unwavering dedication to combating terrorism, noting global leaders' condemnation of the attack and solidarity with India.
title: 'Pahalgam perpetrators will be punished': Top quotes from PM Modi's 'Mann Ki Baat'

description: Union Minister Hardeep Singh Puri strongly condemned Pakistan following the Pahalgam terror attack, asserting that the nation would face severe consequences for its actions. He highlighted Pakistan's declining state and its use of terrorism as state policy. India has taken decisive diplomatic actions, including suspending the Indus Waters Treaty, signaling a firm response to cross-border terrorism.
title: 'Pak will be brought to its knees': Hardeep Singh warns over Pahalgam attack

description: A tragic incident occurred at the Lapu Lapu Day Block Party in Vancouver, where a vehicle struck a crowd, resulting in multiple fatalities and injuries. The Vancouver Police have apprehended the driver and are currently investigating the event that took place during the Filipino community's celebration.
title: Several dead at Vancouver festival, driver arrested: What we know so far

description: Bollywood's King Khan, Shah Rukh Khan, is set to make his grand debut at the Met Gala 2025, marking a historic moment for Indian representation. He will collaborate with celebrated designer Sabyasachi Mukherjee, promising a legendary fusion of Indian craftsmanship and global celebrity. The theme, "Superfine: Tailoring Black Style," sets the stage for a night of unparalleled fashion.
title: Shah Rukh Khan to make his historic Met Gala debut with Sabyasachi

description: Following their crucial victory against Chennai Super Kings, Sunrisers Hyderabad has embarked on a brief retreat to the Maldives. The team's win at Chepauk has revitalized their playoff aspirations, breaking a long-standing losing streak at the venue. Looking ahead, Sunrisers will face Gujarat Titans on May 2, aiming to continue their winning momentum and secure a coveted playoff spot.
title: Sunrisers Hyderabad team jets off to Maldives after their win over CSK
Thiruvananthapuram airport receives bomb threat via email

description: A masked thief has been apprehended for stealing Department of Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem's Gucci handbag, containing cash, passport, and confidential documents, from a DC restaurant. The suspect, believed to be part of an East Coast gang specializing in high-end thefts, executed the crime while Noem dined with family, despite the presence of Secret Service agents.
title: Trump’s top security chief lost her $4,400 Gucci purse — who stole it and how

description: Weeks after a cordial dinner, Bill Maher sharply criticized Donald Trump, cautioning against his flirtation with authoritarianism. Maher referenced Trump's past remarks about exceeding term limits and joked about being a dictator, warning that such jokes can become reality. Despite some conservative support for his anti-wokeness stance, Maher made it clear that his dinner with Trump wouldn't silence his concerns about Trump's potential authoritarian tendencies.
title: Bill Maher torches Trump: 'Flirting with dictatorship doesn’t stay flirting'

description: Cars24, a prominent pre-owned vehicle e-commerce platform, has recently laid off approximately 200 employees across various departments as part of a strategic restructuring. CEO Vikram Chopra stated this decision aims to align the company's structure with long-term objectives, emphasizing it's not a cost-cutting measure. Affected employees will receive severance packages, career assistance, and emotional wellness resources.
title: Cars24 lays off 200 employees: Read what the CEO said

description: Assam Chief Minister Himanta Biswa Sarma condemned Bilawal Bhutto Zardari's remarks against India. Sarma stated that such statements disrespect Bilawal's family sacrifices. India has suspended the Indus Waters Treaty. This action follows a terrorist attack in Jammu and Kashmir. The Cabinet Committee on Security, led by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, made the decision.
title: 'India will hunt down terror': Himanta slams Bilawal Bhutto's remarks

description: Mumbai Indians, riding on a four-game winning streak, face Lucknow Super Giants in a crucial IPL mid-table clash. Both teams are tied at 10 points, battling for a top spot. Mumbai's key players like Rohit Sharma and Hardik Pandya are in top form, while Lucknow relies on their overseas stars.
title: IPL match today: MI vs LSG - all you need to know
Several killed after SUV runs into crowd at Vancouver street festival

description: A sartorial stir erupted at Pope Francis's farewell, as dignitaries seemingly veered from Vatican tradition. Donald Trump, Prince William, and Joe Biden donned blue hues, contrasting with the customary black attire for such events.
title: Why did Trump's, Prince William's attire at Pope Francis' funeral raise eyebrows?

description: Amid escalating tensions following the Pahalgam attack, Pakistani minister Hanif Abbasi threatened India with nuclear retaliation, asserting that 130 missiles are aimed at India. Abbasi's statement followed India's diplomatic actions, including expelling Pakistani officials and halting the Indus Waters Treaty, after the deadly Pahalgam attack that killed 26.
title: '130 missiles kept for India': Pakistan min's open threat over Pahalgam attack

description: Following the deadly Pahalgam attack, authorities in Jammu and Kashmir have intensified their crackdown on terrorism by demolishing the houses of three more active terrorists in Bandipora, Pulwama, and Shopian districts. These actions bring the total number of demolitions to nine, targeting individuals involved in terror activities and linked to groups like Lashkar-e-Taiba.
title: Houses of 3 more terrorists demolished in crackdown as Pahalgam attack probe intensifies

description: Pakistani troops have violated the ceasefire agreement for the third consecutive night by initiating unprovoked firing along the Line of Control in Jammu and Kashmir. Indian Army soldiers responded effectively with small arms fire in the Tutmari Gali and Rampur sectors.
title: Pakistan violates ceasefire for third night, Indian Army responds effectively

description: In J&K's Anantnag, Shahzada Bano's house was demolished after her son, Adil Hussain Thoker, was named a suspect in the Pahalgam attack. Adil's family claims no contact since 2018, when he left for an exam. Bano pleads for his surrender. Security forces searched the home before demolition, detaining Adil's father, brothers, and cousins. Neighbors recall Adil as a dedicated student.
title: ‘Surrender so we can live in peace’: Terrorist Adil’s mother

description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) is investigating FIIT-JEE for financial irregularities and failure to provide promised educational services. Searches revealed the institute collected ₹250 crore from 15,000 students, diverting funds to personal properties and leaving faculty salaries unpaid. Numerous coaching centers were abruptly closed, leading to widespread distress and police FIRs.
title: FIITJEE siphoned off Rs 250cr, failed to deliver quality edu services: ED

description: A fire erupted at approximately 2:30 am on Sunday in Mumbai's Kaiser-I-Hind building, which houses the Enforcement Directorate (ED) office. The fire, confined to the fourth floor of the five-story building, prompted a Level-II emergency response. Firefighters deployed multiple resources, including fire engines and tankers, to contain the blaze, and the cause of the fire remains under investigation.
title: Fire breaks out at ED's Mumbai office, no injuries reported

description: Following the deadly terror attack in Pahalgam, FBI Director Kash Patel assured India of continued support, echoing sentiments from top US leaders like President Trump and Vice President Vance. They condemned the attack and reaffirmed solidarity with India in combating terrorism.
title: 'Evils of terrorism': FBI's Kash Patel offers India 'full support' after J&K attack

description: Sunny Deol's film Jaat saw a rise in earnings on its third Saturday. It earned Rs 1.25 crore, a jump from Friday's Rs 85 lakh. The film faces competition from Akshay Kumar's Kesari Chapter 2. Jaat's total box office collection is Rs 82.85 crore. Sunny Deol has confirmed Jaat 2, promising it will be even better.
title: Jaat box office day 17: Sunny Deol and Randeep Hooda starrer mints Rs 1.25 crore
J&K: Social activist shot by suspected terrorists in Kupwara amid high security alert

description: In a significant admission, Russia confirmed North Korean military personnel are fighting alongside its forces in Ukraine, validating claims from Zelenskyy and South Korea. Valery Gerasimov reported to Putin that North Korean soldiers provided substantial support, operating under a strategic alliance. Putin praised his forces' success in the Kursk region.
title: Russia for first time confirms North Korean troops fighting in Ukraine war

description: Photos circulating on social media purportedly show Donald Trump sleeping during Pope Francis' funeral in Rome, sparking online criticism. Trump was seated alongside Melania Trump and Volodymyr Zelenskyy. Despite the controversy, Trump shared images from the funeral on Truth Social and met with Zelenskyy, commenting on the situation in Ukraine.
title: Was Trump sleeping at Pope Francis' funeral? Viral photos spark debate

description: Donald Trump has urged for free passage for American military and commercial ships through the Panama and Suez Canals, directing Secretary of State Marco Rubio to act immediately. He highlighted the US's historical involvement in these waterways. This comes amid disruptions to Suez Canal traffic due to Houthi rebel attacks and escalating US military actions against them.
title: Trump demands ‘free’ transit for US ships through Panama, Suez canals

description: A massive explosion and fire at Iran's Shahid Rajaei port resulted in 14 fatalities and over 750 injuries. The incident, reportedly linked to a shipment of missile fuel chemicals, occurred near Bandar Abbas during nuclear negotiations with the US.
title: Watch: Explosion at Iran's Shahid Rajaei port kills 14, over 700 injured

description: A de-weeding operation at Bengaluru's Madiwala Lake uncovered a shocking amount of waste, including a refrigerator. The Jaldost team, using NAL's technology, has removed over 20 tonnes of garbage. Locals criticize BBMP's waste management and lack of lake monitoring. NAL highlights the potential for biomass reuse, but BBMP's slow waste removal raises concerns about environmental neglect.
title: De-weeding operation at Bengaluru lake throws up refrigerator
